  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Submitted under ProfileMinimal; intended-use scope is not declared in this package.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-cbp-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-cbp-piv-flowfield"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
